He submits a complaint that an imitation evil spirit has committed a kidnap. Li Jing, the Pagoda−carrying Heavenly King, and his son Prince Nezha have been slack in controlling their women's quarters. He has allowed his daughter to run away and turn into an evil spirit in the Bottomless Cave in Mount Pitfall, where she has lured countless deluded people to their deaths.
She has now carried my master into a remote corner where he cannot be found.
If I had not submitted this complaint I would have been deeply worried that the heavenly king and his son in their wickedness had deliberately incited his daughter to become a spirit and cause general disaster.
