We definitely must leave in a day or two." The marquis refused to let them go, and he ordered many people to prepare a banquet and start building a monastery that very night.
The next day there was a magnificent banquet at which the Tang Priest took the place of honour while the Great Sage Monkey sat beside him with Pig and Friar Sand.
The marquis and his officials high and low passed them cups of wine and dishes of food while fine music was played, and so they were entertained all day.
It was a most happy occasion, and there is a poem to prove it: After long drought the fields received sweet rain; Merchants were travelling along all watercourses.
