The Great Sage set off by his cloud somersault and flew up into mid air.
All the officials in front of the throne hall looked up into the sky and bowed low.
The Great Sage Monkey went straight to the mountain that lay due South.
When the evil spirit had fled in defeat to the mountain and gone into her den she blocked the entrance with boulders and lay hidden there, terrified.
Having looked around for a while and seen no sign of life Monkey felt very impatient, so he made a spell with his hands and said the magic words, calling out the local deity and mountain god to be questioned.
