The evil spirit, who was indeed hiding in there, sprang out with a whoosh, raising her medicine pestle to strike him with.
As Monkey swung his cudgel to parry her blow the mountain deity fell back in terror and the local god fled. From the demon's mouth came abusive grumbles:
"Who told you to bring him here to find me?" She continued to fend off the iron cudgel as she fled up into mid air in a fighting retreat.
Just at the moment of crisis, when it was getting late in the day, Monkey became more vicious than ever and his blows were even harder. He wished he could finish her off with a single stroke.
