Journey to the West The Moon was persuaded, so he pointed at the evil spirit and shouted, "Repent and submit, evil beast!" The Jade Hare rolled on the ground and turned back into her real form.
Indeed she was Gap−lipped and sharp−toothed, Long−eared and with few whiskers.
Her body was covered with jade−coloured fur; When she stretched out her legs she flew over mountains.
